			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>Company</strong></p>
<p>
	GiaSpace is an IT service provider based in Fort Lauderdale Florida, founded in 1998.&nbsp; We specialize in providing technology services, support and management to businesses in South Florida, with our primary focus on small and mid-size businesses in the surrounding area.</p>
<p>
	Our vision: To become the preeminent IT provider for small and mid-size&nbsp;companies in the South Florida area, by providing comprehensive networking and software services.</p>
<p>
	Our mission statement:&nbsp; We assist our clients in achieving maximum benefit from their IT investment by being professional, knowledgeable, reliable, and courteous.&nbsp; We listen, we educate, and we find solutions.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Job Description</strong></p>
<p>
	The Service Desk Technician is a member of the GiaSpace Service Desk team, which provides day to day operational support for our clients.&nbsp; This position will be primarily focused on remote tier 1 support, and some on-site support.&nbsp; The individual will interact directly with a wide range of clients, providing desktop, application, server and network support in a timely and effective manner.&nbsp; He/she will be responsible for tracking and resolving all assigned support requests through effective decision making and problem solving.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	The Service Desk Technician will be part of our Service Desk team, and will report to the Operations Manager.&nbsp; The successful job applicant will present himself/herself in a professional, competent manner, and will communicate effectively with our clients.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	This position also participates in a regular after hours on-call rotation.</p>
<p>
	GiaSpace provides a competitive salary, vacation, and benefits.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Required Skills</strong></p>
<p>
	The successful candidate for this position will possess a degree or diploma related to information technology, with 3+ years of experience providing IT support in a fast paced environment.&nbsp; They will also meet the following requirements:</p>
<p>
	<strong>Personal:</strong><br />
	&bull; Outstanding interpersonal and communication skills in English<br />
	&bull; Enthusiasm for providing outstanding customer service<br />
	&bull; Strong decision making and problem solving skills<br />
	&bull; Presents himself/herself in a highly professional, competent manner<br />
	&bull; Ability to work calmly under pressure, multitask and prioritize<br />
	&bull; Ability to work independently and within a team environment<br />
	&bull; Results and detail oriented<br />
	&bull; Patience to solve technical problems with end users of varying technical aptitudes</p>
<p>
	<strong>Technical:</strong><br />
	&bull; Installation, configuration, and troubleshooting of Microsoft desktop operating systems<br />
	&bull; Installation, configuration, and troubleshooting of Microsoft Office applications<br />
	&bull; Installation, configuration, and troubleshooting of Sonicwall/Cisco firewalls<br />
	&bull; Configuration and troubleshooting of Symantec Backup Exec and StorageCraft ShadowProtect backup software<br />
	&bull; Configuration and troubleshooting of Microsoft servers and software, such as Small Business Server, Active Directory, Exchange and SQL Server<br />
	&bull; Experience with Microsoft Hyper-V and/or VMWare vSphere<br />
	&bull; Experience with Microsoft Terminal Services and Citrix XenApp<br />
	&bull; Experience with ConnectWise or other PSA (Professional Services Automation) system<br />
	&bull; Experience with Zenith or other RMM (Remote Monitoring and Management) system<br />
	&bull; Technical certifications, such as MCSE/MCITP would be considered an asset.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Interested candidates should apply via&nbsp;form.&nbsp; We review all submissions, however only candidates selected for an interview will be contacted.&nbsp; No phone calls, please.</strong></p>
<p>
